
Student Result Management System

A simple Java desktop application to manage student results using Java Swing and MySQL.
This project allows you to Add, View, Update, and Delete student records with automatic calculation of Total, Percentage, and Grade.

Features

	Add new students with their marks.
	
	View all student records in a table.
	
	Update existing student details and marks.
	
	Delete student records.

	Automatic calculation of total marks, percentage, and grade.


Input validation:

	Name cannot be empty.
	
	Marks must be numeric and between 0 and 100.

Technologies Used

	Java SE (Swing for GUI)
	
	MySQL (for storing student records)
	
	JDBC for database connectivity.

Project Structure

		StudentResultManagement/
		│
		├── src/
		│   ├── com/gui/          # GUI classes
		│   │     └── StudentGUI.java
		│   ├── com/dao/          # DAO interfaces
		│   │     └── StudentDAO.java
		│   ├── com/daoimpl/      # DAO implementations
		│   │     └── StudentDAOImpl.java
		│   ├── com/model/        # POJO class
		│   │     └── Student.java
		│   └── com/util/         # Database connection utility
		│           └── DBConnection.java
		│
		├── README.md
		└── .gitignore

Database Setup

		Create a MySQL database named student_db.
		
		Create a table students:
		
		CREATE TABLE students (
		    id INT PRIMARY KEY AUTO_INCREMENT,
		    name VARCHAR(100) NOT NULL,
		    marks1 INT NOT NULL,
		    marks2 INT NOT NULL,
		    marks3 INT NOT NULL,
		    total INT NOT NULL,
		    percentage FLOAT NOT NULL,
		    grade VARCHAR(2) NOT NULL
		);


		Update the DBConnection.java with your MySQL username and password.

How to Run:

		Import the project into Eclipse or any Java IDE.
		
		Add MySQL JDBC connector to your project libraries.
		
		Run StudentGUI.java.
		
		Use the GUI to Add, View, Update, or Delete students.




